#%PAM-1.0
# PAM stack for the tunnel-only sshd (PAM service name: sshd-tunnel).
#
# Deliberately contains NO pam_boks: port 2222 is independent of BoKS, which
# governs port 22 through its own boks_sshd + PAM service. Because this stack
# has a distinct service name, the two daemons do not share PAM state.
#
# The daemon is pubkey-only (PasswordAuthentication no, KbdInteractive no), so
# sshd never invokes the PAM auth phase; account + session still run under
# UsePAM yes. account requires a valid AD account (via SSSD); disabled/expired
# AD accounts are rejected here even though the key is accepted.
auth       required   pam_deny.so
account    required   pam_sss.so
password   required   pam_deny.so
session    required   pam_limits.so
session    optional   pam_sss.so
session    optional   pam_mkhomedir.so umask=0077
